README
------

script 11 and 12 demonstrate a while loop reading from stdin, and
waiting for either "exit", "quit", or "raus" to end the loop.

* script11.sh: using logical operators

* script12.sh: using egrep evaluating the input as text patterns

script13.sh: reading from stdin, and post-processing the output line by
line

anpingen.sh: reading host names from a list, and output its network state

while-passwd.sh: read fields from /etc/passwd, and print them in
different order
